  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACTION FOR PEACEFUL AND CREDIBLE ELECTIONS IN NIGERIA (ACPACE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nigeria&#x2019;s presidential, parliamentary and states gubernatorial and assembly elections, scheduled for February 2015, will be more contentious than usual. Tensions within and between the two major political parties, competing claims to the presidency between regional politicians along religious lines, the monstrous Islamist Boko Haram insurgency and increasing communal violence in several northern states have almost left Nigeria in an explosive situation. 

The dicey situations resulted in Caritas Nigeria taking the initiative to work with the Bishops and other Faith leaders to ensure that the upcoming elections in Nigeria are violent free.  Therefore, through this project Caritas Nigeria will engage more actively with socio-political leaders through a forum that is chaired by the bishop to strengthen the early warning response systems and promote violent free elections.

Also, massive sensitization via the media will further fortify the already existing messages and voices calling for violent free elections in Nigeria.</narrative>
  </description>
